      "writtenOn": "2017-10-26T16:16:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We cannot, this loop is converting two pixels at a time.  The first RGB pixel is used for Y, U, and V, and the second is only used for Y.\n\nChanging white-balance modifies the Y value, so we need to perform it for each pixel.\n\nNote that there\u0027s a bigger optimization that I\u0027ve been eyeing here, which is that _change_white_balance is effectively doing r /\u003d r_scale, g /\u003d g_scale, b /\u003d b_scale, which is a lot of divides, all unnecessary! Computing 1 / r_scale, etc, in advance and then doing multiplies would be significantly faster (I don\u0027t have numbers, but searching has revealed 10-20x faster for multiply vs divide).  However, I\u0027d first want to write tests to verify because this code has been full of surprises :-)",
      "parentUuid": "c2a0d76e_8fd80576",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1083,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 1084,
        "endChar": 79
      },
